briefTitle: Extension of Phase 3 Gene Therapy for Painful Diabetic Neuropathy
officialTitle: Long-term, Prospective, Non-interventional, Extension of a Phase III, Randomized, Placebo-controlled, Multicenter Study to Assess the Safety & Efficacy of Engensis (VM202) in Subjects With Painful Diabetic Peripheral Neuropathy

interventions.name: Long-Term Follow-Up of Patients who Received Engensis (VM202)
Long-Term Follow-Up of Patients who Received Placebo

summary:
The purpose of this study is to explore the overall safety profile and durability of efficacy of Engensis (VM202) in painful diabetic peripheral neuropathy.

All subjects still in follow-up for the VMDN-003 study or who have completed the Day 270 visit within the prior 90 days will be approached to enroll in the long-term safety extension study.

primaryOutcome.measure: Long-term Safety for Engensis Versus Placebo
